description: A first-year coupe with racing stripes, an upgraded 289 V8, and an upgraded five-speed manual transmission â€“ oh yeah! This 1965 Ford Mustang is all the right upgraded fun.  And for those keeping track, this is a rare 65C car.

Crisp lines, great detailing, and plenty of gloss from the modern Red Hot paint job make this one timeless. A first-year pony car is always desirable.  It's the kind of American icon that evokes memories the moment anyone catches sight of the pony on the grille.  So it's hard to go wrong with this classic coupe.  Every piece of brightwork is complete and near pristine, from the wide front bumper, to the side scoops, to the Mustang-branded gas cap.  But more than just a great classic, you also get some great standout upgrades to make this one look more like a GT/Shelby.  This includes the GT grille with fog lights, custom silver stripe package, and Halibrand-style 17-inch wheels.

This Mustang is a true driver's classic.  The interior gets down to business quickly with its deep, dark appearance that has the fresh feeling of investment.  Plus, you have nice upgrades like the AM/FM/CD stereo.  You get all the great iconic features like the dual cowl dash and the three-spoke sports steering wheel with pony logo center cap.  But there's a very unique feature to this interior.  Mustang people instantly recognize that bench seat.  It makes this a rare classic with less than 2.7% of total '65 production had this feature in coupes.

And because you had Shelby-style touches on the outside, this one celebrates even more under the hood with the iconic Cobra air topper and matching valve covers.  And more than just look performance-oriented, this 289 cubic-inch V8 has been upgraded with a Holley four-barrel carburetor and long-tube headers.  Because it's a driver's car, this one wants to make sure you feel connected with the motor and the road.  That's why it has some great modern upgrades like the five-speed manual transmission and directional sport tires.
A hot color, racing stripes, a five speed... and that's before you count this coupe's rarity.  It's impressive this level of distinction can also be so affordable.  Call today!!!

description: Half way through the year 1964, Ford released the first ever Mustang that quickly became an American icon that has carried on throughout the last half century. Their innovative idea was to make a model that was fun and affordable for almost anyone to cruise along in style. This mid-year pony car has inherited modern components from some of the newer models. A full rotisserie restoration was done on this classic Ford where no area was left untouched. Under the hood rests a 5.0L V8 that originated in a 1989 Mustang and was woken up with a mild competition cam, aluminum intake, and 2 1/2Ã¢?Â dual exhaust. Fire it up and drop the C4 automatic transmission into gear. As you lean on the throttle, the tuned-up 5.0 will force you back into your seat but the Z-rated performance tires will assure you stay in control at all times. The modern wheels pay homage to the classic styling from when this car was new and tucked behind those, are a set of disc brakes that were taken from a 2007 Mustang for optimal braking. This Mustang is the best of all worlds with classic styling and modern performance. Take this to your local cruise night or car show and you are guaranteed to turn some heads and have fun doing it! This vehicle is located in our Denver showroom. You can view this 1965 Ford Mustang in greater detail including HD pictures and an HD video of it running and driving at Gatewayclassiccars.com. description: With a V8, A/C, and sunning red paint, it's time for you to get your hands on your dream 1965 Ford Mustang for quite a nice price.

The color of this coupe makes it the perfect standout.  A first-year Mustang dressed in red is iconic, but when you render it in a deeper shade of Black Cherry, it gets extra attention when hanging out with the other classics. No matter if you are across the show field or one-inch away, the investment in this color is instantly apparent.  There's a deep luster and the kind of hard shine that makes it look like this coupe has a top coat made of glass.  To pull off this presentation, you also need super straight body panels.  The total effect gives the first-year Mustang's crisp lines a more sophisticated appearance.  That's backed up by the full trim package, including new bumpers and grille to keep everything shining at its best.  Even the bright of the 14-inch styled steel wheels give this one the kind of distinction you're looking for when you want to stand out from the crowd.

Inside the theme of an upgraded classic presentation continues with the two-tone interior.  The white vinyl seats look great, and they just seem to reinforce the clean presentation of this car.  Plus, the carpets are black so you never have to worry about taking your shoes off before hopping in and going for a drive... and that's exactly what this car was built to do.  It has all the right upgrades to keep everyone happy, including the cup holder center console, AM/FM stereo, and R134a air conditioning.  It all makes for a classic cruiser that's comfortable enough for even the daily commute.

Ford's reliable and perky 289 cubic-inch V8 moves the lightweight Mustang enthusiastically through any traffic â€“ especially with the addition of a four-barrel carburetor on top. The engine bay has all the right style upgrades like the bright intake, valve covers, bracer bar, and air topper. There was even a Monte Carlo bar added for extra rigidity and flair.  These motors are extremely reliable, parts are readily available, and performance is very good â€“ all of which gives you an underlying feeling of carefree classic motoring.  Adding to this go-anywhere sensation in this the three-speed automatic transmission and the modern grip of Hankook Optimo tires.

Complete with build receipts and maintenance records, the first-generation Ford Mustang is a true classic car for those who like driving.  Add in the stellar presentation, and you soon realize that vintage style distinction can be quite affordable. Don't miss out, call today!
